             rdfs:label "creep test piece chemical composition"@en ;
             skos:definition "creep test piece composition is a chemical composition data item that is specification of the chemical composition of a creep test piece which participates in a creep testing process. It is an information content entity about the elemental makeup of the material, specifying the proportions of chemical elements present. It appears as a table of element symbols with corresponding weight percent (wt.%) or atomic percent (at.%) values, or as inline compositional text, typically found in the materials section or a dedicated composition table of a scientific paper, and explicitly refers to the chemical makeup of the target creep test piece." .


