             rdfs:label "creep test standard"@en ;
             skos:definition "A creep test standard is a standard that is concretized as a plan which is intended to realize a creep testing process. It establishes the set of guidelines, criteria, and norms governing the execution of a creep test. It appears as a designator string referencing an internationally recognized testing norm (e.g., \"ASTM E139\", \"ASTM E 8M-94a\", \"ISO 204\"), typically found in the experimental methods, testing conditions, or specimen preparation section of a scientific paper, and explicitly refers to the normative framework under which the target creep test was conducted." .


