             rdfs:label "specified creep temperature datum"@en ;
             skos:definition "A specified creep temperature datum is an input specification that is concretized as a temperature which changes a quality in a creep testing process. It prescribes the test temperature applied as a controlled input condition during the creep experiment. It appears as a numeric value with a temperature unit (e.g., \"650°C\", \"750 K\"), typically found in the testing parameters table, experimental conditions section, or figure axes of a scientific paper, and explicitly refers to the temperature at which the target creep test was conducted." .


