             rdfs:label "specified creep stress datum"@en ;
             skos:definition "A specified creep stress datum is an input specification that is concretized as a mechanical stress which is realized in a creep testing process. It prescribes the applied stress imposed on the creep test piece as the primary loading input. It appears as a numeric value with a stress unit (e.g., \"625 MPa\", \"150 MPa\"), typically found in the testing parameters table, experimental conditions section, or figure axes of a scientific paper, and explicitly refers to the initial applied stress under which the target creep test was conducted." .


