             rdfs:label "creep rupture time value"@en ;
             skos:definition "A creep rupture time value is a scalar value specification that specifies the value of the stress rupture time of a loading process which is part of a creep testing process. It quantifies the total duration from the application of load to specimen fracture. It appears as a numeric value with a time unit (e.g., \"159.74 h\", \"68779 h\"), typically found in the creep properties table, results section, or Larson–Miller plots of a scientific paper, and explicitly refers to the time to rupture of the target creep test piece." .


