                                                  ]
                             ] ;
             rdfs:label "percentage initial plastic extension value"@en ;
             skos:definition "A percentage initial plastic extension value is a scalar value specification that specifies the value of the percentage initial plastic extension realized in a creep testing process. It quantifies the irreversible deformation occurring immediately upon load application before the creep stage, relative to the original gauge length. It appears as a numeric value expressed as a percentage, typically found in the creep deformation breakdown table of a scientific paper, and explicitly refers to the initial plastic extension at the onset of the target creep test." .


