                                                  ]
                             ] ;
             rdfs:label "percentage plastic extension value"@en ;
             skos:definition "A percentage plastic extension value is a scalar value specification that specifies the value of the percentage plastic extension realized in a creep testing process. It quantifies the total irreversible deformation of the specimen accumulated during the creep test, relative to the original gauge length. It appears as a numeric value expressed as a percentage, typically found in the creep deformation data table of a scientific paper, and explicitly refers to the plastic extension component recorded during the target creep test." .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/cto/CTO_0000036
:CTO_0000036 rdf:type owl:Class ;
             owl:equivalentClass [ owl:intersectionOf ( obo:OBI_0001931
                                                        [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
