                                                                         ]
                                                                       ) ;
                                                    rdf:type owl:Class
                                                  ]
                             ] ;
             rdfs:label "percentage creep extension value"@en ;
             skos:definition "A percentage creep extension value is a scalar value specification that specifies the value of the percentage creep extension realized in a creep testing process. It quantifies the time-dependent deformation of the specimen that occurs specifically under sustained load at elevated temperature, relative to the original gauge length. It appears as a numeric value expressed as a percentage, typically found in the creep strain or creep deformation table of a scientific paper, and explicitly refers to the creep-specific extension accumulated during the target creep test" .


