                                                                       ) ;
                                                    rdf:type owl:Class
                                                  ]
                             ] ;
             rdfs:label "stady state creep rate value"@en ;
             skos:definition "steady state creep rate value is a scalar value specification that specifies the value of the creep rate which is a process attribute of a creep testing process. It quantifies the minimum or steady-state strain rate at which the specimen deforms during the secondary creep stage. It appears as a numeric value with a unit of inverse time (e.g., \"0.96 × 10⁻⁴ s⁻¹\", \"1.04 × 10⁻⁴ 1/s\"), typically found in the creep properties table, results section, or Norton power-law fitting data of a scientific paper, and explicitly refers to the steady-state creep rate measured during the target creep test." .


###  https://w3id.org/pmd/cto/CTO_0000038
