             rdfs:label "creep test piece identifier"@en ;
             skos:definition "A creep test piece identifier is an object identifier that denotes a creep test piece which participates in a creep testing process. It uniquely designates a specific specimen used in a creep experiment. It appears as an alphanumeric code, label, or sample name (e.g., \"HT1\", \"SSM_100\", \"CLH4663\"), typically found in the specimen description, experimental setup table, or results section of a scientific paper, and explicitly refers to the individual creep test piece under investigation." .


