             rdfs:label "creep test piece manufacturing description"@en ;
             skos:definition "A creep test piece manufacturing description is a textual description that denotes a manufacturing process which performed for preparing the sample before creep testing process. It describes the fabrication route applied to produce the creep test piece prior to testing. It appears as a text string or structured narrative describing methods such as casting, forging, additive manufacturing, or powder metallurgy (e.g., \"LPBF (EOSINT M290) + HIP\", \"VIM + ESR\"), typically found in the materials and methods section or specimen preparation section of a scientific paper, and explicitly refers to the manufacturing history of the target creep test piece." .


