             rdfs:label "creep test piece solutionizing description"@en ;
             skos:definition "A creep test piece solutionizing description is a textual description that denotes a solutionizing heat treatment process which perfomed before creep testing process. It describes the high-temperature homogenization treatment applied to the creep test piece before testing. It appears as a text string specifying temperature, duration, and cooling method (e.g., \"1095°C, 1 h/AC\", \"HIP: 100 MPa, 1175°C, 4 h\"), typically found in the heat treatment, specimen preparation, or materials section of a scientific paper, and explicitly refers to the solutionizing step applied to the target creep test piece." .


