             rdfs:label "creep test piece delta precipitate size value"@en ;
             skos:definition "A creep test piece delta precipitate size value is a scalar value specification that specifies the value of the size of a delta precipitate which is a member of a microstructure that is part of a creep test piece participating in a creep testing process. It quantifies the average or representative dimension of delta phase particles in the material. It appears as a numeric value with a length unit (e.g., \"2 μm\", \"500 nm\"), typically found in the microstructure characterization or TEM/SEM analysis section of a scientific paper, and explicitly refers to the delta precipitate size in the target creep test piece." .


